FBIS4-16710 "drsov075_d_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-075 Daily Report 16 Apr 1994 Regional Affairs Tataria To Seek Balance in Forming New Government Tataria To Seek Balance in Forming New Government MK1604133094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 16 Apr 94 p 3 MK1604133094 Moscow SEGODNYA Russian BFN [Unattributed ADS report in the "Provincial Chronicle" column] [Text] Kazan -- Tataria Vice Premier Ravil Muratov has stated that a balance of "promarketeers" and conservatives will be ensured in the new government which is to be formed before September. According to him, there is a need to cut the number of vice premiers, replace the Cabinet of Ministers' sectoral departments with an institution of referents, and reduce the number of ministries and committees. Muratov also considers it necessary to create an analytical center to formulate government strategy. The vice prime minister proposes setting up a so-called Republican Agricultural Chamber, regarding it, along with Tataria's Chamber of Industry and Commerce, as the main opponents to the Cabinet of Ministers.
